Common Pantry Van Analysis

Hi! This page is meant to summarize Common Pantrys van usage. Between November 2020 and July 8, 2021, the Common Pantry van has been driven 620.8 miles (and there are 1791.7 miles on the van total). We will look at the data from November through the end of June, during which the van has traveled 603 miles.

Common Pantry Van Miles per Month

Common Pantrys van traveled the most miles in March and May 2021 with over 100 miles each month. 35.5 of the 101.9 miles in March came from a trip to and from Winnetka Congregational Church for a donation pickup. 73.1 of the 118.5 miles driven in May resulted from traveling to and from Matteson Prairie.

Without the trips to WCC and Matteson Prairie, the distribution of miles driven per month is adjusted below.

Mileage Breakdown

You may be wondering what these 600+ miles were driven for. It is broken down visually in the graph below.

Here is what each category represents. Additionally, check out the table below for the exact monthly mileages to and from each destination category.

Grocery: miles driven to and from Aldi, Harvestime, Jewel, and Whole Foods

Pick-up: miles driven to pick up donations from donor homes and organizations (such as Cradles 2 Crayons, Ravenswood Elementary, Share Our Spare, and more), as well as to pick up additional items for clients (for example, First Slice and Restaurant Depot).

Random: this counts mileage for several random trips the van was used for, including to and from Staples, Ace Hardware, Matteson Prairie, the car wash, and any trips with a missing location.

Garage-pantry: solely counts the mileage the van traveled between Common Pantry and the garage.

Drop-off: miles driven to drop of donations. This includes Salvation Army, Friendship Center, RCS, Concordia, Swedish, and more.
